{{Infobox person | name = Raquel Freire | image = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1973|6|22}} | birth_place = [[Porto]], [[Portugal]] | nationality = Portuguese | other_names = | occupation = [[Film director]], [[screenwriter]], [[novelist]] | known_for = }} '''Raquel Freire''' (born 22 June 1973, in [[Porto]]) is a Portuguese [[film director]], [[screenwriter]] and [[novelist]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://cvc.instituto-camoes.pt/cinema/personalidades/per084.html|title= FREIRE, Raquel|accessdate= 30 November 2014|work= Cinema Português|publisher= [[Instituto Camões]]|language= Portuguese}}</ref><ref name=sapo>{{cite web |url= https://noticias.sapo.pt/lusa/artigo/891074fd9f23eec68b1955.html|title= Cinema: "Veneno cura", de Raquel Freire, abre trilogia sobre a intimidade e o amor|author= [[Agência Lusa]]|date= 9 January 2009|accessdate= 30 November 2014|work= noticias.[[sapo.pt]]|language= Portuguese}}</ref><ref name=ruadebaixo>{{cite web |url= http://www.ruadebaixo.com/raquel-freire-entrevista.html|title= RAQUEL FREIRE ENTREVISTA|date= June 2013|accessdate= 30 November 2014|work= ruadebaixo.com|language= Portuguese}}</ref>
